World Bank Bonds Support Sustainable Development
Sustainable Development recognizes that growth must be both inclusive and environmentally sound to reduce poverty and build shared prosperity for today’s population and to continue to meet the needs of future generations. It is efficient with resources and carefully planned to deliver both immediate and long-term benefits.

Sustainable Investing in World Bank Bonds
World Bank bonds are the primary funding source for member country project loans. Through its activities in the capital markets, the World Bank is able to fund projects in member countries in areas such as health and education, gender equality, and environmental protection and climate change activities.

40 Years of World Bank Bonds in Japan
2011 marks the fortieth anniversary of the World Bank’s first bond issue in Japan. That issue, a JPY 11 billion bond launched in June, 1971, represented an important step in the evolution of Japan’s relationship with the World Bank.
